summary:
Head of the Global Accounts Department at KYOCERA Document  Solutions Europe.

Strongly self-motivated, results-driven international business manager with extensive international and intercultural exposure, a passion for continuous improvement and an ample range of management skills, from strategic planning and vision definition to operational control, solution definition and due diligence.

Overall responsibility in the last three years for KYOCERA EMEA managed print services global accounts: in charge of global account strategy definition and execution, business development,  P&L, and sales pipeline and forecast.  

Whilst at KYOCERA, I have led business development that resulted in the award of multi-year managed print services (MPS) contracts from global leaders in the automotive, food and beverages, steel, and manufacturing verticals worth in excess of tens of millions of euros in revenue for the group, with a steady increase in profitability and customer loyalty and satisfaction.

Before joining KYOCERA Europe, I led successful global, cross-functional teams for over 8 years in pursuing mission critical election automation and information technology projects in Africa, Asia, Europe and Latin America as global head of bid management at Smartmatic.  I used my intercultural relationship skills and extensive international exposure to ensure the teams under my responsibility delivered on commitments in multi-million Euro/dollar projects.

Over 25 years of experience in business development, international bidding, partner management and design & delivery of ICT projects across several industries/verticals.

Coming from a  programming and system design background, I transitioned to Solution Architecture and IT Process Management over the course of 13 years as a systems and IT consultant at Unisys Corporation and Hewlett-Packard Consulting and Services, prior to becoming Worldwide Business Support Manager at Smartmatic.

Key skills /experience: 
* Global account planning and management;
* International sales and business planning and development;
* Relationship-based (Miller-Heiman) & value-based Agile selling (Richardson);
* International/global bid and proposal cycle and strategy management;
* Multi-Geography lead qualification and opportunity management;
* Complex ICT project costing & pricing;
* Digital transformation and transition;
* CRM and proposal automation;
* Commercial intelligence analysis;
* Partner management;
* High-performance team management and leadership.

profile_positions.description:
Responsible for the global accounts strategy and operation at KYOCERA Document Solutions in the EMEA region:

1. Define and execute global account strategy;
2. Manage global accounts from the financial (P&L), operational (SLA compliance), contractual (KPIs and penalty management) and commercial (pipeline and forecast) perspectives;
3 Support all KDE subsidiaries in pursuits of major (Global 2000, FT1000) accounts in their territories; 
4. Coordinate global account management with Asia-Pacific and the Americas.
5. Coordinate vertical market (industry) development;

1. Define and execute the opportunity qualification and bid management processes for Kyocera document solutions' global accounts business in the EMEA region;
2. Create and develop relationships with internal and external customers, and with business partners and customers in over 85 countries;
3. Define the bid review cycle from kick-off to contract signing to ensure process effectiveness, timely feedback and continuous improvement;
4. Lead pricing processes through modeling, intelligence gathering, benchmarking;
5. Lead and close contractual negotiations, supported by legal and other departments;
6. Ensure timely and effective coordination with sales operations, finance and customer service departments for efficient sales and post-sale operations;
7. Help define the approach to  knowledge management to leverage company experience;

* Lead and manage the bid-to-win proposal cycle for the EMEA region with a win rate of 60%. Direct report to the regional president;
* Manage internal and external relationships with providers, partners and customers during the bid/proposal cycle;
* Conduct regular bid reviews during the cycle and post-submission to ensure effective feedback and continuous improvement;
* Support product and business strategy definition and execution;
* Support other regions through knowledge management process to leverage company experience;
* Support costing and pricing processes through modelling,  intelligence gathering, knowledge sharing, benchmarking and more;

* Support sales strategy execution worldwide with direct report to the head of Worldwide Sales;
* Lead bid-to-win proposal cycle for large (USD 50+ million) international bids in EMEA, Asia Pacific and Latin America;
* Promote continued sales organizational transformation to achieve business goals and create competitive advantages;
* Collaborate with maximizing financial contribution from sales activities;
* Oversee the opportunity management process;
* Supervise sales activities and provide direct support for sales regions: Americas, Asia-Pacific and EMEA.

•	Manage technical support and operations in support of the Galileo Argentina, Brazil, Curacao and Venezuela subsidiaries;
•	Provide SLA-compliant services for over 1,500 terminals in over 300 travel agencies with a team of 10 technicians and outsourced telecommunications services.
•	Design and manage the CRM and incident / technical support ticketing systems.
